# System Monitor API

A lightweight system monitoring API built with FastAPI and Docker.  
It provides basic system metrics such as disk usage, memory usage, and CPU information.

---

## 1. Project Overview

This project is a simple backend service that exposes system metrics through RESTful APIs.

It is designed to:
- Practice FastAPI development
- Understand service structure (routes, services, utils)
- Learn Docker-based deployment
- Implement logging and error handling

---

## 2. Features

- Disk usage monitoring
- Memory usage monitoring
- CPU process count
- Unified response format
- Global exception handling
- Basic logging support
- Dockerized deployment

---

## 3. Project Structure

sys_api/
├── main.py # Entry point
├── utils.py # Common utilities (logging, response, command execution)
├── routes/
│ └── metrics.py # API routes
├── services/
│ └── system_metrics.py # Business logic
